      • list

        public static PropertyDescriptor list(String name,
                                      PlyDataType countType,
                                      PlyDataType dataType)
        Creates a PropertyDescriptor for a list property.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the property.
        countType - The PlyDataType used to store the length of a list. This must not be a floating point type.
        dataType - The PlyDataType used to store the entries in a list.
        Returns:
        A new PropertyDescriptor.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if countType == null or if countType is a floating-point type.
